movie.title: Daughters of the Sexual Revolution: The Untold Story of the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders
movie.title_english: Daughters of the Sexual Revolution: The Untold Story of the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders
movie.title_long: Daughters of the Sexual Revolution: The Untold Story of the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders (2018)
movie.description_intro: The never-before-told story of Suzanne Mitchell, the fiercely-loyal den mother of the original Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders. Seen by many as regressive and exploitative, this diverse sisterhood of small-town "girls next door" became a controversial pop culture phenomenon at the height of the Sexual Revolution, changing the game of football -- and America -- forever.

movies.title: Frailty
movies.summary: FBI agent Wesley Doyle is startled by the declaration of youngster Fenton Meiks about how his father's delusions required him and his brother, Adam to become his 'demon-slaying' murder accomplices. But when Doyle accepts to be shown concealed victim graves, the plot twists in the present just as gruesome.

movies.title: Unpregnant
movies.summary: A 17-year old Missouri teen named Veronica discovers she has gotten pregnant, a development that threatens to end her dreams of matriculating at an Ivy League college, and the career that will follow.

movies.title: Summer of Sam
movies.summary: Spike Lee's take on the "Son of Sam" murders in New York City during the summer of 1977 centering on the residents of an Italian-American Northeast Bronx neighborhood who live in fear and distrust of one another.

movies.title: Isadora
movies.summary: A biography of the dancer Isadora Duncan, the 1920s dancer who forever changed people's ideas of ballet. Her nude, semi-nude, and pro-Soviet dance projects as well as her attitudes on free love, debt, dress, and lifestyle shocked the public of her time.
